{"title":"Fox Introduces Their First Visor-free Helmet, the Crossframe Pro for Downcountry & Gravel","link":"https://bikerumor.com/fox-first-visor-free-helmet-crossframe-pro-downcountry-gravel/","date":1683040641000,"content":"<p>With a history in motocross and gravity-fueled mountain biking, Fox Racing is known for its aggressive aesthetic. So it may raise a few eyebrows then as they prepare to enter new territory for the brand. Call it what you wish – downcountry, gravel, aggro XC, whatever the nomenclature, the upcoming Crossframe Pro is ready for it. And according to Fox, it’s their first-ever/ visor-free helmet. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Crossframe Pro helmet\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear6.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Crossframe Pro helmet side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear10.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Crossframe Pro helmet front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear9.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Crossframe Pro helmet back\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear8.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Crossframe Pro helmet inside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear7.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Even though it is technically visor-free, the Crossframe Pro still has a pronounced brow. Kind of like a visor that’s integrated into the EPS foam. On the underside of that brow, there are functional vents that are part of the 22 total vents on the helmet. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Inside, you’ll find a MIPS liner with a BOA retention system, as well as dual-density Varizorb EPS foam for improved impact protection. The helmet also features premium features like a removable and washable Ionic+ liner, rubberized sunglass grippers, and a Fidlock SNAP helmet buckle. Claimed weights are listed as 330-390g for S-L, with our medium pre-production sample weighing 346g. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Flexor Ascent clothing for gravel downcountry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear3.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Along with the Crossframe Pro Helmet, Fox is introducing a line of clothing for the same category in the Flexair Ascent line. Somewhere between baggy and tights, the clothing has a more aerodynamic cut than typical Fox clothing. Designed to be ultra light and cool, the shorts feature a fairly short 10″ inseam, and jerseys will be offered in SS &amp; LS. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We got an early sample to check out and so far both the clothing and the helmet have been surprising in a good way. The fit on the clothing is excellent, and it all feels incredibly comfortable. I’m looking forward to getting some more miles on these this summer. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Dropframe Pro</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Dropframe Pro\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear13.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Dropframe Pro front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear12.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Fox Dropframe Pro back\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fox-Crossframe-pro-dropframe-pro-downcountry-gravel-gear11.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new downcountry/gravel gear may have been the star of the show, but the new Dropframe Pro is worth a look as well. Previously, Fox updated the Proframe RS with many of the features from the Proframe, and now those updated trickle down to the Dropframe Pro as well. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 3/4 shell has an updated headform with a BOA fit system and MIPS, and meets the NTA-8776 eBike helmet certification. The visor has three poisitons and is compatible with goggles, and you’ll find an Ionic+ anti-microbial liner and cheek pads plus a Fidlock magnetic buckle. Claimed weight is listed as 620-710g. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>All of the products above will be available later this year with pricing to be announced. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.foxracing.com\" target=\"_blank\">foxracing.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/fox-first-visor-free-helmet-crossframe-pro-downcountry-gravel/\">Fox Introduces Their First Visor-free Helmet, the Crossframe Pro for Downcountry &amp; Gravel</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"082df9bdb0b84a665c5da2755410bb9643094eba150d84c3c48ca85ee234a572","category":"Cycling"}